01:17.756 --> 01:20.459
(GIRL SINGING) <i>♪ When I was young ♪</i>

01:20.460 --> 01:22.931
<i>♪ And scared of the Lord ♪</i>

01:22.932 --> 01:27.809
<i>♪ My mother Would sing me a song ♪</i>

01:28.544 --> 01:33.386
<i>♪ A tune that I keep In a sacred place ♪</i>

01:33.721 --> 01:38.129
<i>♪ Because I know That
my life won't be long ♪</i>

01:39.240 --> 01:44.050
<i>♪ It tells of the place Where you go ♪</i>

01:44.767 --> 01:49.544
<i>♪ When your time here
on Earth is through ♪</i>

01:50.387 --> 01:54.128
<i>♪ A beautiful place We call heaven ♪</i>

01:55.665 --> 01:59.037
<i>♪ Is it true ♪</i>

01:59.038 --> 02:03.446
<i>♪ Please God I pray that it's true ♪</i>

02:05.484 --> 02:06.920
(WHEEZING)

02:09.058 --> 02:10.595
(STOPS BREATHING)

02:34.509 --> 02:35.945
(SOBBING)

02:52.682 --> 02:58.060
<i>♪ 'Cause once this land
Was heaven on Earth ♪</i>

02:58.423 --> 03:02.565
<i>♪ Green hills were all You could see ♪</i>

03:03.299 --> 03:08.175
<i>♪ But now it's soot
And steel and brick ♪</i>

03:08.176 --> 03:12.351
<i>♪ So it looks more Like hell to me ♪</i>

03:13.386 --> 03:17.962
<i>♪ And each day brings
More and more suffering ♪</i>

03:18.731 --> 03:23.039
<i>♪ And each night is silence and fear ♪</i>

03:23.741 --> 03:28.049
<i>♪ And I wake To the
sound of your voice ♪</i>

03:28.951 --> 03:31.823
<i>♪ But you're not here ♪</i>

03:33.192 --> 03:36.667
<i>♪ Why aren't you here? ♪</i>

03:40.173 --> 03:45.083
<i>♪ So now I lay me Down to sleep ♪</i>

03:45.851 --> 03:48.288
<i>♪ I pray the Lord ♪</i>

03:48.289 --> 03:51.361
<i>♪ My soul to keep ♪</i>

03:51.362 --> 03:56.172
<i>♪ Please let me die Before I wake ♪</i>

03:56.640 --> 04:00.848
<i>♪ So the Lord My soul, can take ♪</i>

04:02.217 --> 04:07.060
<i>♪ Then maybe I'll finally find you ♪</i>

04:07.595 --> 04:12.237
<i>♪ 'Midst the beauty Of paradise ♪</i>

04:12.972 --> 04:17.815
<i>♪ And you'll sing not
of dying But living ♪</i>

04:20.153 --> 04:24.763
<i>♪ Wouldn't that be nice? ♪</i>

04:26.198 --> 04:31.142
<i>♪ Wouldn't that be nice? ♪</i>

04:45.894 --> 04:48.214
It was unholy carnage.

04:48.242 --> 04:51.448
Ripped through them like old
Jack the Ripper himself.

04:51.486 --> 04:53.590
And there were two of them?

04:53.815 --> 04:55.534
(BOY) Like wolves they were.

04:55.925 --> 04:57.861
Teeth wet with blood.

04:57.862 --> 05:00.968
Fistfuls of flesh they ate and ate.

05:02.066 --> 05:04.004
So he comes for me...

05:05.411 --> 05:06.981
the Wolf of God.

05:07.561 --> 05:10.253
And the other one, the grey wolf.

05:10.597 --> 05:12.400
That I can't say.

05:13.894 --> 05:16.097
Shall I send some of
these ones after him?

05:16.098 --> 05:17.167
No.

05:19.543 --> 05:21.179
No. He's too strong.

05:53.640 --> 05:55.043
What do you fear?

05:57.347 --> 05:58.684
I don't know what you mean.

05:59.243 --> 06:00.947
I can smell it on you.

06:02.154 --> 06:03.357
He's coming...

06:04.586 --> 06:06.222
your Mr. Chandler.

06:07.300 --> 06:09.037
I have reason to fear him.

06:10.715 --> 06:12.986
He is foretold as my singular enemy.

06:14.782 --> 06:17.386
VANESSA: Fear not old prophecies.

06:17.387 --> 06:18.724
We defy them.

06:20.736 --> 06:22.607
We make our own heaven...

06:24.034 --> 06:25.838
and our own hell.

06:31.750 --> 06:33.152
Let him come.

06:34.087 --> 06:37.327
He and I shall write
the ending in blood.

06:38.195 --> 06:40.701
As it was always going to be.

06:43.774 --> 06:45.076
(GASPS)

06:48.349 --> 06:49.552
(SOFTLY) Vanessa.

06:50.554 --> 06:51.823
(GRUNTS)

06:57.300 --> 06:58.436
You.

07:02.846 --> 07:04.450
How did I not know?

07:06.227 --> 07:07.931
None of my tribe knew.

07:10.042 --> 07:14.017
When the moon became
full, I would steal away

07:14.042 --> 07:17.282
and I would find the enemy's camp.

07:17.307 --> 07:20.614
And I would wait for
the wolf to devour me.

07:22.164 --> 07:26.674
I believed that this was
a great gift from God.

07:27.349 --> 07:29.253
That I had been given...

07:30.262 --> 07:32.434
the power to save my people.

07:36.091 --> 07:37.393
I was wrong.

07:38.534 --> 07:40.437
The soldiers kept coming.

07:41.208 --> 07:43.480
My people kept dying.

07:48.464 --> 07:51.637
But then a vision was sent to me.

07:51.807 --> 07:54.245
About a man with a true heart.

07:54.270 --> 07:55.539
A son.

07:56.249 --> 08:00.391
And only then did I
understand my true purpose.

08:01.571 --> 08:03.340
It was not to save my people.

08:03.365 --> 08:06.673
It was to give you the
power to save all people.

08:09.506 --> 08:11.009
You did this to me?

08:13.757 --> 08:15.588
You made me this monster?

08:15.613 --> 08:17.377
I claimed you for God.

08:17.661 --> 08:18.930
(GRUNTS)

08:20.107 --> 08:23.648
Do you know how many
people I've murdered?

08:23.673 --> 08:26.057
- How many have suffered?
- (CHOKING)

08:26.082 --> 08:28.219
Their blood is on my soul!

08:29.917 --> 08:32.423
You have poisoned my heart.

08:32.448 --> 08:35.419
I have given you

08:35.443 --> 08:37.648
the power to save her!

08:40.874 --> 08:41.909
(GRUNTS)

08:43.445 --> 08:45.216
(RAGGED BREATHING)

08:49.657 --> 08:51.961
Graves will overflow.

08:51.986 --> 08:53.756
The rivers will run with blood.

08:53.808 --> 08:56.246
And darkness will consume the earth.

08:56.271 --> 08:58.743
Only one man can stop this.

09:00.569 --> 09:05.111
I, alone, understand the
sins you have committed.

09:06.458 --> 09:08.228
The pain you carry.

09:09.331 --> 09:12.971
But all your life you
have run from this pain.

09:12.972 --> 09:14.574
You ran from your father.

09:14.575 --> 09:16.478
You ran from your tribe.

09:17.615 --> 09:18.717
Tonight...

09:19.719 --> 09:20.721
you stop running.

09:21.681 --> 09:25.221
Tonight, you accept the
destiny that God has granted.

09:27.766 --> 09:30.972
I will do whatever I
need to, to save her.

09:38.489 --> 09:39.992
RENFIELD: <i>Promises he has made.</i>

09:41.596 --> 09:43.867
Delicious promises.

09:44.735 --> 09:47.289
Tasty morsels I shall have.

09:47.314 --> 09:49.920
None more tasty than you, my dear.

09:49.945 --> 09:52.482
Oh, stop, you'll turn my head.

09:52.483 --> 09:53.867
(LAUGHS) Oh, yes,

09:53.892 --> 09:56.875
he'll give you to me, as my reward.

09:57.761 --> 09:58.797
Hold on...

09:59.464 --> 10:00.633
what's that?

10:00.634 --> 10:03.609
I'll have none of your witch doctoring!
(GRUNTS)

10:03.634 --> 10:06.305
Move a muscle, I'll
thrash the skin off you.

10:06.311 --> 10:09.150
(RENFIELD YELLING) <i>Leave my
fucking brain alone, you cunt!</i>

10:09.752 --> 10:11.321
(SCREAMING)

10:19.137 --> 10:20.606
Where is Miss Ives?

10:20.607 --> 10:23.269
She's happy where she is. Leave her be.

10:23.294 --> 10:24.214
Where is she?

10:24.215 --> 10:26.820
She'll never be happy
sitting by the fire

10:26.845 --> 10:28.709
in your loveless mansion.

10:29.343 --> 10:31.014
Let her be.

10:32.531 --> 10:35.402
And let this wretched world end

10:36.104 --> 10:37.541
and let another begin.

10:38.762 --> 10:40.533
The world of the night.

10:41.296 --> 10:45.406
The world of the bat and
the owl and the spider.

10:47.502 --> 10:49.839
The blessed dark.

10:52.571 --> 10:54.107
(PANTING)

11:05.362 --> 11:07.333
(TAPPING CANE)

11:14.455 --> 11:17.019
He's a handsome man, your master.

11:17.044 --> 11:19.617
Ah. Radiant.

11:19.820 --> 11:21.570
And he's been kind to you.

11:21.595 --> 11:24.903
Bountiful with the gore, he's been.

11:25.443 --> 11:26.745
I should like to meet him.

11:26.770 --> 11:27.800
You will.

11:27.825 --> 11:30.531
(LAUGHS) You all will.

11:30.689 --> 11:32.159
Won't you take me to him?

11:32.184 --> 11:33.653
Clever girl.

11:34.663 --> 11:36.534
Clever girl.

11:36.559 --> 11:37.594
Shh!

11:39.925 --> 11:41.529
You're safe with me.

11:43.740 --> 11:45.709
Let's walk there, shall we?

11:45.710 --> 11:47.213
(RAGGED BREATHING)

11:52.815 --> 11:54.051
What's that I see?

11:54.076 --> 11:56.146
You don't want to see
what I see, Doctor.

11:59.475 --> 12:01.746
Once seen, it can't be unseen.

12:02.041 --> 12:03.677
Where are we, Renfield?

12:03.702 --> 12:05.472
What are we seeing?

12:07.286 --> 12:09.023
Is it the fog still?

12:13.815 --> 12:16.190
Or is it the clouds of opium now?

12:16.800 --> 12:20.300
Oh, the smell in this place is noxious.

12:21.140 --> 12:23.308
From the fish stalls, I think.

12:23.854 --> 12:27.061
And what is it we hear?

12:27.655 --> 12:31.534
The tap, tap, tap...

12:31.602 --> 12:34.058
of the tattoo pen into the pink flesh,

12:34.769 --> 12:37.714
and the drops of blood as they drip,

12:38.210 --> 12:41.984
drip, drip to the floor.

12:50.007 --> 12:51.243
What is this place?

12:51.408 --> 12:53.679
Where I go to find my master.

12:55.294 --> 12:57.466
But they're always watching me.

12:59.870 --> 13:01.607
Take my hand, please.

13:10.270 --> 13:12.374
I have sinned here, Mother.

13:13.520 --> 13:16.024
I have smoked opium with yellow devils

13:16.049 --> 13:19.490
and planted my seed in unworthy whores.

13:21.301 --> 13:22.838
Can you forgive me?

13:23.371 --> 13:24.373
Of course.

13:25.275 --> 13:26.311
Yes.

13:27.686 --> 13:30.458
Please, take me to your master.

13:33.853 --> 13:34.855
You know,

13:36.740 --> 13:38.511
I wish we had been friends,

13:38.536 --> 13:39.638
you and I.

13:41.692 --> 13:43.910
If I had known a friend
like you in my life,

13:44.169 --> 13:46.239
I mightn't have ended this way.

13:47.593 --> 13:49.363
So pitiful and pale.

13:50.182 --> 13:52.340
No one ever believed in me, you see.

13:53.542 --> 13:54.801
No one cared.

13:55.508 --> 13:56.977
Help me, Renfield.

13:58.477 --> 13:59.913
I'll be your friend.

14:01.711 --> 14:03.080
I think you will.

14:04.485 --> 14:05.379
Thank you.

14:07.667 --> 14:09.069
Then we'll go on.

14:09.802 --> 14:11.138
Where are we going?

14:12.814 --> 14:14.183
The dead place.

14:37.907 --> 14:39.844
DORIAN: You would have
been proud of her.

14:41.243 --> 14:43.581
She remained your faithful
acolyte until the end.

14:46.759 --> 14:48.095
She had no fear.

14:49.679 --> 14:50.848
The others?

14:52.383 --> 14:53.451
Gone.

14:54.287 --> 14:56.090
To where they came from, I assume.

15:05.567 --> 15:08.639
So my great enterprise comes
to no more than this.

15:10.285 --> 15:11.454
(SNIFFLES)

15:12.340 --> 15:14.344
One more dead child.

15:15.329 --> 15:17.299
Be kind to yourself, Lily.

15:18.636 --> 15:21.709
Passion will undo the best of
us and lead only to tragedy.

15:22.711 --> 15:24.947
It's ever thus for those
who care so deeply.

15:24.948 --> 15:27.086
Better not to care at all, Dorian?

15:28.656 --> 15:29.958
In my experience.

15:34.968 --> 15:36.905
I don't want to live like that.

15:37.329 --> 15:40.832
You'll learn to, in time.

15:47.994 --> 15:49.664
(SNIFFLING)

16:03.968 --> 16:07.099
Do you not yet comprehend the
wicked secret of the immortal?

16:11.164 --> 16:14.496
All age and die, save you.

16:16.447 --> 16:20.082
All rot and fall to dust, save you.

16:20.661 --> 16:22.865
Any child you bear becomes a crone

16:23.402 --> 16:25.440
and perishes before your eyes.

16:26.204 --> 16:27.840
Any lover withers and shrinks

16:27.841 --> 16:31.180
into incontinence and
bent, toothless senility.

16:32.028 --> 16:33.131
While you...

16:34.153 --> 16:35.723
only you...

16:37.292 --> 16:38.495
never age.

16:40.098 --> 16:41.434
Never tire.

16:42.537 --> 16:43.873
Never fade.

16:46.512 --> 16:47.680
Alone.

16:53.291 --> 16:56.497
But after a time you'll lose the
desire for passion entirely...

16:58.836 --> 17:01.073
for connection with anyone.

17:01.659 --> 17:04.799
Like a muscle that atrophies
from lack of use.

17:06.852 --> 17:08.320
And one day

17:10.258 --> 17:12.496
you'll realize you've become like them.

17:15.670 --> 17:17.540
Beautiful and dead.

17:19.974 --> 17:21.679
You have become a perfect,

17:22.082 --> 17:24.420
unchanging portrait of yourself.

17:28.127 --> 17:30.332
An eternity without passion?

17:31.467 --> 17:34.674
Without affection? Caring for nothing?

17:38.916 --> 17:42.089
Small price to pay for such
immortal perfection, isn't it?

18:14.788 --> 18:16.023
Goodbye, Dorian.

18:20.487 --> 18:22.524
I hope they watch over you.

18:26.645 --> 18:28.314
You'll be back.

18:33.124 --> 18:34.561
And I'll be here.

18:39.537 --> 18:41.140
I'll always be here.

19:08.394 --> 19:11.199
DR. JEKYLL: You are painfully
true to form in every instant.

19:11.224 --> 19:13.782
Weak and sentimental as
you have always been!

19:13.807 --> 19:15.096
I should never have left
you alone with her!

19:15.121 --> 19:16.891
It was a monstrous idea!

19:17.150 --> 19:18.227
We're well out of it!

19:18.252 --> 19:19.352
Fine words from you,

19:19.377 --> 19:22.104
who traffics in stolen
corpses and dead flesh!

19:22.150 --> 19:23.552
Oh, I'll show you monsters, Victor!

19:23.718 --> 19:25.690
Walk down that corridor
and open any door.

19:26.098 --> 19:27.868
"Monstrous" you may call it,

19:27.900 --> 19:29.269
but I'll continue my work

19:29.558 --> 19:31.997
until I cure every inmate
in this wretched place.

19:32.075 --> 19:33.463
And then you'd be happy?

19:33.862 --> 19:35.314
And then you'd get the
acclaim and affection

19:35.315 --> 19:36.449
that's eluded you your whole life?

19:36.450 --> 19:37.815
Yes!

19:37.885 --> 19:40.457
If you think scientific achievement

19:40.605 --> 19:43.543
will bring you acceptance
or even esteem,

19:43.861 --> 19:46.408
an entree into proper society,

19:46.761 --> 19:48.364
you're deluding yourself.

19:49.577 --> 19:51.247
That's not the world we live in.

19:52.249 --> 19:54.854
I create my own world.

19:55.488 --> 19:57.158
I create my own self.

19:59.196 --> 20:00.598
And one day,

20:00.599 --> 20:02.776
one day, all of you will understand

20:03.048 --> 20:05.186
that of which I am capable.

20:07.613 --> 20:08.815
I'm sorry, Henry.

20:09.784 --> 20:12.389
It's a dark road ahead for you, I fear.

20:15.461 --> 20:17.065
And for you, old man?

20:17.800 --> 20:19.168
(SIGHING)

20:19.169 --> 20:21.106
There is no road ahead for me.

20:23.745 --> 20:26.150
There will always be a place
for you here, Victor,

20:27.213 --> 20:28.750
in the heart of science.

20:33.999 --> 20:35.702
Now, it is time for my rounds.

20:35.703 --> 20:37.372
Good day, my friend.

20:39.544 --> 20:40.980
Oh, there is one thing more.

20:42.148 --> 20:43.919
This day is not a total loss for me.

20:44.821 --> 20:46.891
My hateful father has died, you see.

20:51.400 --> 20:53.169
At long last,

20:53.170 --> 20:56.443
the estate and the title
are finally mine.

20:59.349 --> 21:02.322
So I'm not so far from the
aristocracy as you might think.

21:04.627 --> 21:07.265
Then I should properly
call you by your title.

21:08.267 --> 21:09.504
It seems only fitting.

21:12.244 --> 21:13.714
Good day then...

21:15.268 --> 21:16.570
Lord Hyde.

21:34.352 --> 21:36.456
DR. SEWARD: <i>What do we see now?</i>

21:36.457 --> 21:38.895
The alley by the spice
market is where we turn.

21:39.931 --> 21:41.365
(GASPS)

21:41.366 --> 21:45.675
(SNIFFING) Ah, can you smell it now?

21:45.676 --> 21:46.878
What?

21:47.680 --> 21:49.316
The rotting corpses.

21:49.984 --> 21:52.790
This was a slaughterhouse
in days long past.

21:55.294 --> 21:57.765
They butchered so many poor animals.

21:57.766 --> 21:59.670
I can still hear them screaming.

22:00.776 --> 22:02.513
I can still see them hanging there.

22:03.477 --> 22:06.960
And the blood. The torrents of blood.

22:06.985 --> 22:09.189
And your master, is he here?

22:11.506 --> 22:13.075
Do you not feel him?

22:13.698 --> 22:15.636
And where is Vanessa?

22:16.270 --> 22:17.672
With him.

22:17.673 --> 22:19.577
They're in love, Doctor.

22:22.415 --> 22:24.286
Have you ever been in love?

22:24.820 --> 22:25.656
Where is she?

22:25.681 --> 22:27.885
I don't think I've ever been in love.

22:28.008 --> 22:30.012
And now I probably never will be.

22:31.568 --> 22:33.437
Do you love me, Doctor?

22:40.586 --> 22:42.222
Renfield.

22:42.353 --> 22:44.658
Mr. Renfield. Come back to me now.

22:44.683 --> 22:45.685
- Wake up.
- (RENFIELD GASPS)

22:48.500 --> 22:50.137
I know where she is.

22:54.780 --> 22:56.855
By now, Mr. Chandler must
be back at the house.

22:56.880 --> 22:58.283
Sir Malcolm!

22:58.469 --> 23:00.238
Good God, it's Doctor Frankenstein.

23:00.263 --> 23:01.667
What are you doing here of all places?

23:01.728 --> 23:03.397
Later. I'll explain later.

23:03.664 --> 23:04.741
But will you come with us now?

23:04.766 --> 23:06.803
- Vanessa's in danger.
- Yes, of course.

23:06.804 --> 23:09.877
We've got to meet Ethan. We
haven't a moment to lose.

23:15.254 --> 23:16.791
(MAN COUGHING)

23:25.676 --> 23:29.751
He seems smaller, does he not?

23:32.790 --> 23:35.796
Like a bird more than a child.

23:37.408 --> 23:41.653
With such delicate, thin bones.

23:44.792 --> 23:48.667
And skin like a Chinese paper lantern.

23:51.508 --> 23:54.079
When I was dressing him
in his Sunday clothes,

23:56.036 --> 23:58.575
and even those so threadbare and meager,

24:01.079 --> 24:03.216
I thought, "How is it possible

24:03.217 --> 24:06.189
that life could be so
cruel to one so young?"

24:09.797 --> 24:11.365
He had not enough years in him

24:11.366 --> 24:12.770
to suffer so mightily.

24:15.854 --> 24:17.289
But it is ever so.

24:21.186 --> 24:23.490
Flint is the heart of the world.

24:30.697 --> 24:32.100
Spend your time with him.

24:35.466 --> 24:37.704
I'll arrange for the
funerary men to come.

24:39.489 --> 24:41.761
He'll have a proper burial, at least.

24:43.865 --> 24:45.868
The dignity he was denied in life

24:45.869 --> 24:47.305
will be his in death.

24:48.073 --> 24:49.275
MARJORIE: <i>No.</i>

24:51.714 --> 24:52.950
CREATURE: I'm sorry?

24:53.818 --> 24:55.020
No.

24:56.524 --> 24:58.060
I don't want him buried.

25:00.565 --> 25:02.034
Marjorie, it must be done.

25:04.305 --> 25:07.478
Hold his hand now and
make your farewells.

25:08.413 --> 25:09.617
Why should I?

25:11.219 --> 25:12.890
Why should either of us?

25:15.762 --> 25:17.766
He's not lost to us yet.

25:22.643 --> 25:25.473
Take him to Doctor Frankenstein.

25:26.445 --> 25:28.248
Let him perform his miracles.

25:29.188 --> 25:31.594
He will bring our son back.

25:33.665 --> 25:35.333
You don't know what you're saying.

25:35.334 --> 25:38.172
He pulled you from the grave
and brought you back to us.

25:38.173 --> 25:39.777
He can do the same for Jack.

25:40.712 --> 25:43.115
We can love our son again, husband!

25:43.116 --> 25:45.521
- Don't ask this.
- He can live again!

25:45.522 --> 25:48.393
- Don't even think it!
- I will have my son back!

25:49.530 --> 25:51.066
(SOBBING) I will love him again,

25:52.234 --> 25:55.274
love him better, and stronger,

25:56.009 --> 26:00.584
and he will not get sick
and he will not bleed

26:00.585 --> 26:02.254
and he will not die!

26:03.297 --> 26:05.209
Let me love him again!

26:05.595 --> 26:08.467
And have all the humanity
burned out of him?

26:09.903 --> 26:14.112
To become an unholy freak as
he who stands before you?

26:15.949 --> 26:18.320
I see the husband who I love, no other.

26:18.461 --> 26:19.798
You see a monster.

26:21.292 --> 26:24.331
A grisly undead thing.

26:24.332 --> 26:25.602
That is what I am.

26:26.804 --> 26:28.707
That is what Dr. Frankenstein

26:28.708 --> 26:29.976
has made of me.

26:29.977 --> 26:32.048
Only because you believe it so.

26:33.353 --> 26:35.222
He can live again.

26:36.657 --> 26:38.326
(SOFTLY) Don't ask this.

26:40.799 --> 26:42.736
To make him suffer as I did?

26:44.439 --> 26:45.909
Those little bones?

26:47.913 --> 26:49.148
That face?

26:51.486 --> 26:57.230
To become something so
unnatural, so hated.

26:57.231 --> 26:58.333
No.

27:00.304 --> 27:01.439
Please.

27:04.345 --> 27:05.715
Hear me now.

27:07.552 --> 27:09.188
Take him from this place.

27:10.692 --> 27:15.033
Return with him alive,
or don't return at all.

27:17.304 --> 27:20.343
I could not bear to look at your face

27:20.344 --> 27:22.380
if you let him remain like that

27:22.381 --> 27:24.018
when you could save him.

27:26.991 --> 27:28.126
Marjorie.

27:32.301 --> 27:33.805
Bring him back as he was,

27:35.909 --> 27:38.614
or turn from this house forever.

28:18.368 --> 28:19.804
This is it?

28:19.805 --> 28:22.535
According to the old maps, the
slaughterhouse is down that alley.

28:23.303 --> 28:26.527
This whole block's been condemned,
so God knows what we'll discover.

28:26.825 --> 28:27.821
But whatever happens...

28:27.846 --> 28:30.416
Find Vanessa. That's all that matters.

28:30.417 --> 28:31.786
Yes.

28:31.787 --> 28:33.590
You take the front.

28:33.591 --> 28:35.528
Kaetenay and I will find our own way in.

28:36.095 --> 28:37.632
SIR MALCOLM: You're sure that's wise?

28:38.500 --> 28:39.903
We work best alone.

28:42.943 --> 28:46.081
It has been an honor to hunt with you.

28:46.082 --> 28:49.823
You would have made a mighty Apache.

28:50.490 --> 28:52.027
I had a mighty teacher.

28:53.496 --> 28:54.733
Good luck.

29:00.878 --> 29:02.882
You all know what we're facing.

29:06.189 --> 29:08.960
Dr. Seward, we can't
look after you inside.

29:08.961 --> 29:10.764
I'm a New Yorker, Sir Malcolm.

29:10.765 --> 29:13.236
We know our way around random gunplay.

29:16.242 --> 29:17.846
Come on.

29:30.037 --> 29:31.540
(RATS SQUEAKING)

29:52.816 --> 29:54.185
(DOOR CREAKING)

30:54.287 --> 30:55.757
DR. SWEET: Sir Malcolm.

30:56.939 --> 30:58.308
It can be no other.

31:00.116 --> 31:02.854
And your name is known to me as well.

31:02.855 --> 31:05.192
One of them at least.

31:05.193 --> 31:07.097
They are many, my names,

31:07.765 --> 31:10.203
like the carrion circling Golgotha.

31:11.272 --> 31:12.774
Dracula, then.

31:12.775 --> 31:15.680
And you've come freely
into the dragon's cave.

31:15.681 --> 31:17.184
All of you.

31:17.819 --> 31:20.222
Brave or foolhardy,

31:20.223 --> 31:21.627
I can't say...

31:22.528 --> 31:25.000
but we shall feed well tonight.

31:25.500 --> 31:26.703
"We"?

31:27.872 --> 31:30.544
All the children of the Mother of Evil.

31:51.887 --> 31:55.928
- Where is she?
- She is no longer yours.

31:57.297 --> 31:59.367
- Leave this place.
- Where is Vanessa?

31:59.368 --> 32:01.439
She's not yours! She's mine!

32:06.983 --> 32:08.119
But...

32:09.254 --> 32:11.092
she wishes you to live.

32:12.557 --> 32:17.199
So leave, now, while I allow it.

32:22.447 --> 32:24.451
(GROWLING)

32:48.802 --> 32:52.722
Before we go, answer me a question.

32:54.179 --> 32:56.216
My daughter, Mina...

32:56.703 --> 32:58.372
It was you who turned her?

32:59.188 --> 33:00.223
Yes.

33:01.593 --> 33:02.662
Why?

33:03.496 --> 33:06.035
She was meant to bring Vanessa to me.

33:07.270 --> 33:10.442
My daughter's life meant
no more than that?

33:10.443 --> 33:12.180
No more than that.

33:14.654 --> 33:17.091
Although, her flesh was sweet.

33:18.363 --> 33:19.800
And I enjoyed her.

33:29.983 --> 33:31.786
(GROWLING)

33:38.165 --> 33:41.170
- You should go.
- Not a chance.

33:41.171 --> 33:44.111
We're all doomed in this place.

33:44.712 --> 33:46.883
Makes a change for a Tuesday, though.

33:49.589 --> 33:50.824
Fuck him.

33:53.329 --> 33:55.333
I die proudly alongside all of you.

33:58.874 --> 34:00.209
(SNARLING)

34:02.548 --> 34:03.617
(GRUNTS)

34:04.752 --> 34:05.888
(GRUNTING)

34:14.036 --> 34:15.039
(GRUNTING)

34:21.452 --> 34:22.554
Duck!

34:23.089 --> 34:24.190
(GRUNTS)

34:27.163 --> 34:28.366
(GROANING)

34:35.213 --> 34:36.583
(SNARLING)

34:47.538 --> 34:48.540
(HISSING)

34:58.492 --> 34:59.529
(SCREAMS)

35:05.039 --> 35:06.475
(YELLING)

35:14.124 --> 35:15.326
(SNARLING)

35:17.197 --> 35:19.101
(GUN FIRING)

35:28.052 --> 35:30.089
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

35:32.528 --> 35:33.697
(SNARLING)

35:37.505 --> 35:38.507
(GROWLING)

36:11.305 --> 36:12.708
Where is she?

36:30.611 --> 36:31.779
(GRUNTING)

36:37.223 --> 36:38.727
(GRUNTING)

37:52.875 --> 37:55.379
It hurts me more than
I thought it would...

37:56.616 --> 37:57.951
seeing you.

38:01.124 --> 38:02.561
You need to come with me...

38:03.630 --> 38:04.698
now.

38:06.134 --> 38:07.403
And go where?

38:08.205 --> 38:11.077
They will hunt me to the end of days.

38:11.078 --> 38:12.914
I can protect you.

38:12.915 --> 38:17.256
No, you can't. No one can.

38:19.227 --> 38:20.664
Then we'll fight him.

38:21.144 --> 38:24.031
It's not him, it's me.

38:25.288 --> 38:28.562
Look at me. This is what I am.

38:28.587 --> 38:31.125
And this is what I've done.

38:31.150 --> 38:34.256
Brought this terrible
darkness to the world.

38:35.894 --> 38:37.063
Vanessa.

38:40.002 --> 38:41.304
Please.

38:42.140 --> 38:43.442
Vanessa.

38:44.912 --> 38:46.181
And where is she?

38:46.983 --> 38:49.722
When did we lose her, Ethan?

38:51.258 --> 38:53.460
She was standing in a quiet room,

38:53.796 --> 38:55.766
gazing up at a cross.

38:55.767 --> 38:58.506
She reached out, took
it from the wall...

39:00.142 --> 39:02.413
and put it in the fire.

39:05.486 --> 39:07.558
And then she was lost.

39:08.626 --> 39:10.329
And so alone.

39:12.166 --> 39:13.937
You are not alone.

39:14.638 --> 39:15.974
You never were.

39:18.212 --> 39:20.382
I have stood at the very edge.

39:21.184 --> 39:23.690
I have looked into the abyss.

39:24.357 --> 39:27.998
If I'd taken one more step,
I would have fallen.

39:29.735 --> 39:32.674
But no matter how far
I ran away from God,

39:34.143 --> 39:36.682
he was still waiting ahead.

39:40.122 --> 39:42.961
- Not for me.
- For us all.

39:50.476 --> 39:52.380
My battle must end.

39:52.948 --> 39:54.217
You know that.

39:54.991 --> 39:57.288
Or there will never be peace on Earth.

40:00.187 --> 40:02.025
Let it end.

40:07.310 --> 40:08.712
Don't ask it.

40:08.713 --> 40:10.280
I don't have to.

40:10.391 --> 40:12.361
You know you have a destiny.

40:12.386 --> 40:14.189
It's why we first met.

40:14.190 --> 40:16.127
It's why you're here now.

40:16.321 --> 40:18.808
You must help me defeat
the forces of darkness

40:18.833 --> 40:21.470
and deny them their prize for all time.

40:21.471 --> 40:22.574
No!

40:26.414 --> 40:29.835
Please... Ethan.

40:30.189 --> 40:31.792
(SOBBING SOFTLY)

40:32.794 --> 40:34.263
Let it end.

40:59.848 --> 41:01.251
With a kiss.

41:04.257 --> 41:05.760
(SLOWLY) With a kiss.

41:11.295 --> 41:12.632
With love.

41:15.045 --> 41:16.381
With love.

41:40.938 --> 41:42.423
Our Father,

41:44.605 --> 41:46.306
who art in Heaven,

41:46.307 --> 41:48.646
- Hallowed be thy name.
- (MOUTHING)

41:50.148 --> 41:51.652
Thy Kingdom come...

41:52.353 --> 41:53.837
(BOTH) Thy will be done,

41:54.427 --> 41:56.699
on Earth as it is in heaven.

41:58.398 --> 42:00.985
Give us this day our daily bread,

42:01.559 --> 42:03.821
and forgive us our trespasses.

42:04.188 --> 42:07.462
As we forgive those who
trespass against us.

42:08.355 --> 42:11.294
(SNIFFLING) Lead us not into temptation,

42:11.692 --> 42:13.461
but deliver us from evil.

42:14.297 --> 42:16.415
For thine is the Kingdom,

42:17.044 --> 42:19.550
and the Power and the Glory,

42:20.440 --> 42:22.612
for ever and ever.

42:23.883 --> 42:25.152
Amen.

42:29.795 --> 42:30.930
(GUN FIRES)

42:41.752 --> 42:43.388
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

42:51.434 --> 42:52.870
Oh, Ethan...

42:56.615 --> 42:57.917
I see...

43:01.475 --> 43:02.911
our Lord.

43:27.276 --> 43:29.046
(CHOKING)

43:32.554 --> 43:34.156
(GASPING)

43:37.897 --> 43:39.467
(MUMBLES AND GASPS)

45:39.206 --> 45:40.910
SIR MALCOLM: In India,

45:42.947 --> 45:44.349
where I traveled,

45:44.529 --> 45:47.035
they have such colorful gods.

45:48.264 --> 45:49.800
A dozen blue arms.

45:51.438 --> 45:52.875
And bejeweled.

45:53.936 --> 45:57.910
A dazzling and exhausting
panorama of life.

45:59.514 --> 46:02.319
Of lives lived again and again.

46:04.732 --> 46:07.304
Of reincarnated souls.

46:09.675 --> 46:12.013
Do you think such a thing is possible?

46:13.188 --> 46:15.326
It would be cruel for
her to suffer more.

46:18.017 --> 46:19.386
She's at peace.

46:21.290 --> 46:22.927
FRANKENSTEIN: Yes.

46:24.864 --> 46:26.333
You're right.

46:30.094 --> 46:31.498
Dear Miss Ives.

46:44.390 --> 46:45.827
(SIGHS) I'll see you tomorrow then.

46:46.608 --> 46:47.944
Thank you, Doctor...

46:50.048 --> 46:51.083
Victor.

47:13.327 --> 47:14.864
(WHISPERING) Is he all right?

47:16.167 --> 47:17.269
He will be.

47:17.904 --> 47:19.339
And you?

47:26.086 --> 47:27.322
(SIGHING)

47:42.987 --> 47:44.691
(DOOR OPENS)

47:48.064 --> 47:49.567
(DOOR CLOSES)

48:53.929 --> 48:55.799
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

49:14.537 --> 49:15.806
(SIGHS)

49:21.537 --> 49:23.013
And what now?

49:25.337 --> 49:26.810
(SIGHING) Yeah.

49:29.065 --> 49:31.403
Never have I so wanted to run away.

49:34.161 --> 49:37.702
On some hunt or expedition
to Africa, India.

49:40.923 --> 49:42.693
Anywhere but here.

49:46.500 --> 49:48.170
- Will you?
- No.

49:49.545 --> 49:51.716
I must find my life without her.

49:54.316 --> 49:57.388
Miss Ives was the last
link to who I was.

49:59.226 --> 50:02.419
I must find out who I
am yet going to be.

50:05.453 --> 50:07.089
Oh, I will miss her

50:09.279 --> 50:10.916
to my bones.

50:18.234 --> 50:19.804
Will you stay, Ethan?

50:26.225 --> 50:27.761
You're my family.

51:55.696 --> 51:59.804
CREATURE: <i>"There was a
time when meadow, grove,</i>

51:59.829 --> 52:01.533
<i>and stream...</i>

52:02.519 --> 52:06.159
<i>The earth, and every
common sight, to me...</i>

52:07.707 --> 52:11.220
<i>did seem appareled in celestial light.</i>

52:16.470 --> 52:20.321
<i>The glory and the freshness of a dream.</i>

52:23.146 --> 52:26.930
<i>It is not now as it hath been of yore.</i>

52:29.994 --> 52:31.998
<i>Turn whereso'er I may,</i>

52:32.831 --> 52:34.802
<i>by night or day,</i>

52:35.739 --> 52:37.759
<i>the things which I have seen</i>

52:38.377 --> 52:40.314
<i>I now can see no more.</i>

53:26.139 --> 53:27.910
<i>But there's a tree,</i>

53:29.247 --> 53:30.984
<i>of many, one.</i>

53:34.790 --> 53:37.729
<i>A single field which I have looked upon.</i>

53:40.350 --> 53:44.158
<i>Both of them speak of
something that is gone.</i>

53:52.124 --> 53:55.732
<i>The pansy at my feet doth
the same tale repeat.</i>

54:00.358 --> 54:03.274
<i>Whither is fled the visionary gleam?</i>

54:06.554 --> 54:07.915
<i>Where is it now,</i>

54:09.641 --> 54:13.448
<i>the glory and the dream?"</i>

